OL,3,CAurigny defends airfares as Guernsey
OL,4,Chas different 'requirements'
OL,6,FGuernsey airline Aurigny has defended
OL,7,Fthe cost of its fares after a report
OL,8,Ffound that travellers in the Bailiwick
OL,9,Fare paying up to 30% more for flights
OL,10,Fthan those in Jersey and the Isle of
OL,11,FMan.
OL,13,FThe report by Frontier Economics and
OL,14,Fcommissioned by Guernsey's government
OL,15,Fwas published last week.
