OL,3,CAurigny defends airfares as Guernsey
OL,4,Chas different 'requirements'
OL,6,FAnother factor is a lack of commercial
OL,7,Fcompetition for Aurigny which is the
OL,8,Fonly airline to regularly have direct
OL,9,Fflights to the UK from Guernsey and
OL,10,FAlderney.
OL,12,FAt the end of last year, Guernsey's
OL,13,FPolicy and Resources Committee also
OL,14,Fcut the Public Service Obligation
OL,15,F(PSO) subsidy by #500,000 after it was
OL,16,Ffound to be significantly over budget,
OL,17,Fmeaning Alderney flight fares were
OL,18,Fpushed up further.
